thread.title: Twitter reacts as Utes top Cal 30-24 in battle of unbeatens
thread.title_full: Twitter reacts as Utes top Cal 30-24 in battle of unbeatens

author: Holli Joyce, KSL.com Contributor
title: Twitter reacts as Utes top Cal 30-24 in battle of unbeatens
text:
By | Posted 
SALT LAKE CITY — In front of 47,798 fans, the Utah football team fought hard to keep its undefeated record. The Utes (5-0, 2-0 Pac-12) remain the only Pac-12 team with a perfect record after a 30-24 win over Cal (5-1, 2-1). 
Booker should be offensive POW and the whole Ute defense (but probably Domo) should get defensive POW. — Paul Yoachum (@yokester74) 
BREAKING: Utah has a defense, a very good defense. — Ute Central (@utecentral) 
#WHATISGOINGONCITY — MUSS Emeritus (@MUSSEmeritus) 
Dear Utah defense: WE SALUTE YOU!!! Sincerely, #CALvsUTAH — 5-0 #BeatASU (@ScottyP30) 
Death. Taxes. Marcus Williams INT. — Chris Howard (@utahckh) 
Marcus WILLIAMS is everywhere! First a pick, now a fumble recovery!! Let's g ! #CALvsUTAH — 5-0 #BeatASU (@ScottyP30) 
Domo is a baller. — Christian Cox (@ChristianCox94) https://t.co/d8dl7HK4rJ — College GameDay (@CollegeGameDay) 
As if it's easy to do, Booker rushed for a season-high 222 yards on 34 carries with two touchdowns. It was his second 200-yard game — pic.twitter.com/GP3ny6tENU — Sydney Evans (@sydster126) 
If you're going to hit him, just know he hits back #goutes — Gerber Maeser Prep (@Gerbz_Maeser) 
Now that's a Booker run!! — Chris Howard (@utahckh) 
The fanciest tip toeing you ever did see. TOUCHDOWN! — Avery Mills (@alynn422) 
Cal is a great team and the UTES D is legit 5 interceptions on a future NFL QB Solid game Solid! — Brian Smiley (@Smileyguy1)
